1)	Write a program to interchange the largest and the smallest number in an array.
Answer=>

# Python program to interchange the largest and smallest number in an array

# Define the array (list of numbers)
arr = [10, 5, 20, 8, 15]

# Finding the index of the smallest and largest elements
min_index = arr.index(min(arr))  # index of smallest no.
max_index = arr.index(max(arr))  # index of largest no.

#  Print the original array
print("Original array is :", arr)

# Swaping the smallest and largest elements
arr[min_index], arr[max_index] = arr[max_index], arr[min_index]

# Print the updated array
print("Array after swapping largest and smallest:", arr)

