2)	In a small company there are five salesmen. Each salesman is supposed to sell three products. Write a program using a 2D array to
    print (i) the total sales by each salesman and (ii) total sales of each item

Answer=>

# Create a 2D array  to store  data
# Rows = 5 salesmen, Columns = 3 products
# Each inner list represents one salesmanâ€™s sales for 3 products
sales = [
    [100, 200, 150],   # Salesman 1
    [80, 120, 100],    # Salesman 2
    [90, 160, 130],    # Salesman 3
    [110, 140, 120],   # Salesman 4
    [95, 105, 125]     # Salesman 5
]

#Print total sales by each salesman
print("Total sales by each salesman:")
for i in range(5):  # Loop through each salesman
    total = sum(sales[i])  # Sum of all products sold by salesman i
    print(f"Salesman {i+1}: {total}")

#Print total sales of each item
print("\nTotal sales of each product:")
for j in range(3):  # Loop through each product
    total = 0
    for i in range(5):  # Loop through each salesman
        total += sales[i][j]  # Add sales of product j by salesman i
    print(f"Product {j+1}: {total}")

