5)	Write a program which illustrates the use of a pointer to a three-dimensional array.

Answer=>

# Python program to show how a "pointer" (reference) works with a 3D array

#  Create a small 3D array (2 blocks, 2 rows, 2 columns)
array = [
    [ [1, 2], [3, 4] ],
    [ [5, 6], [7, 8] ]
]

#  Make another variable that points to the same array
pointer = array  # This is like a pointer (both refer to the same data)

#  Print the array using the pointer
print("Array using pointer:")
print(pointer)

# Change one value using the pointer
pointer[0][0][0] = 99  # Change the first value

#Print the original array to show that it changed
print("\nOriginal array after change through pointer:")
print(array)

